Garry Monk has described his old pal and mentor Brendan Rodgers as the ‘perfect man’ to lead Liverpool, calling him an ‘inspiration’.

That affection will be temporarily forgotten on Monday evening when Liverpool host Swansea at Anfield.

But such is the friendship between Rodgers and the former defender he managed at Swansea, the Liverpool boss has agreed to let Monk’s side use their Melwood training ground before next Saturday’s FA Cup tie at Tranmere.

