But there has been a recent upturn, with Monk saying: ‘Brendan is one of the most mentally strong people I know. He is the perfect man for that job.

‘Every manager will go through difficult moments — I know I will — and he is coming through it and producing good results and the team are playing a lot better,’ he added.

 

